# The most common is the relational database
# In a relational database, tables are made up of rows, which represent instances of a given entity, and columns, which represent attributes of each entity
# A relational database is made up of relations or tables which are the set of columns, and these tables also contain rows
# We tell the database what sort of information it contains. That might be a number or a string of text. It could be a date, a true or false value, or even a chunk of binary data that represents a file.
